						<div class="postbody">I'm kinda on the fence about it though, is it better to fire the IRQ on the first row of the tile, or on the last row?
<br />
<br />Maybe FE can fire on the first row, and FD can fire on the last row?
<br />In this case, you'd be looking for two addresses: 0FE0/1FE0 and 0FDF/1FDF.
<br />
<br />Alternatively, you could have a 4-bit latch, and just look for 0FEn/1FEn with n being the value of the latch. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /> That way, you could specify which row of tile FE you want the IRQ to fire on. (and which plane, though that's only makes a 2-pixel difference)</div>

