				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I didn't realize why MMC2 and MMC4 use tile $FD and $FE, and not $FF, but after talking with kevtris today I learned the PPU will be doing dummy reads to tile $FF when there are less than 8 sprites to fetch.
<br />
<br />I've been curious about having my CPLD board support the next CPLD step up, I believe I could fit a CPU-cycle counter IRQ by dropping on a 72-macrocell in place of a 36-cell one.  I probably could support it on the board, it'd just cost a few extra bucks for that version.  I do like the idea of having that, then you can do all sorts of fun stuff with the $4011 register.</div>

					
							<br /><br />
							<span class="gensmall">Last edited by <a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=10" style="color: #AA0000;" class="username-coloured">Memblers</a> on Fri May 06, 2011 11:43 pm, edited 2 times in total.</span>
						<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
